  "local_port": 52372,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Bank Accounts: How do I know whether my bank account is linked to my Aadhaar card or not?",
  "response": "To check if your bank account is linked to your Aadhaar card, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Check Your Bank Statement**: Sometimes, banks mention the Aadhaar number on the bank statement if it is linked. You can check your recent bank statements to see if your Aadhaar number is mentioned.\n\n2. **Bank's Online Portal**: Most banks provide an option to check the Aadhaar linking status through their online banking portal. Log in to your bank's net banking account and look for options like \"Aadhaar Seeding Status\" or similar in the service requests or profile section.\n\n3. **Mobile Banking App**: Similar to the online portal, you can also check the status through your bank\u2019s mobile app. Navigate to the section where you can view your account details or service requests.\n\n4. **SMS Service**: Some banks offer an SMS service to check the Aadhaar linking status. You can send an SMS in the specified format (which can usually be found on the bank's website or by contacting customer service) to the designated number provided by your bank.\n\n5. **Visit the Bank Branch**: You can visit your bank branch and ask the bank officials to check if your Aadhaar is linked to your bank account. Make sure to carry your Aadhaar card and any other required identification.\n\n6. **UIDAI Website**: You can also check the status on the UIDAI website (uidai.gov.in). Go to \"My Aadhaar\" and choose \"Aadhaar Services,\" then select \"Check Aadhaar & Bank Account Linking Status.\" You will need to enter your Aadhaar number and the security code to proceed.\n\n7. **Call Customer Care**: You can call your bank's customer care number and ask them to check if your Aadhaar is linked to your bank account. You may need to provide some personal details for verification.\n\nIf your Aadhaar is not linked to your bank account and you need to link it, you can do so by submitting a copy of your Aadhaar card at your bank branch, through the bank's online portal, or via the methods specified by your bank.",
